definitions.definition: To extend over and partly cover something.
examples: The mouse-mat overlapped the edge of the desk.

definitions.definition: To co-occur , to happen at the same time.
To have an area , range , character or function in common .
examples: The two maps overlapped at the east and west edges.

definitions.definition: Of sets : to have some elements in common.
examples: The set (all men) overlaps the set (vegetarians).

definitions.definition: To have some similar nucleotide sequences.
An illusion of depth is created when one object partially covers another.
